# Titanic Survival Prediction 🚢

## Project Overview
A Machine Learning model that predicts whether a 
Titanic passenger survived or not based on their 
age, sex, class, and fare.

## Results 🎯
- **Accuracy: 83%**
- Model: Random Forest Classifier
- Dataset: Real Titanic data (891 passengers)

## What I did 📋
- Loaded real Titanic dataset
- Cleaned missing values (Age, Cabin, Embarked)
- Converted text to numbers (Sex, Embarked)
- Trained Random Forest model
- Achieved 83% accuracy

## Technologies Used 🛠️
- Python
- Pandas
- NumPy
- Scikit-learn

## How to Run 🚀
1. Open titanic_project.ipynb in Google Colab
2. Run all cells
3. See 83% accuracy!

